Brazilian Stock Movers: BM&FBovespa, Brasil Foods, Usiminas

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-02-18T14:38:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/brazilian-stock-movers-bm-fbovespa-brasil-foods-usiminas.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:30 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa index rose 0.3 percent to 67,865.37.    BM&FBovespa SA  (BVMF3 BS) gained 1.1 percent to 12.03
reais. The operator of Latin America’s biggest securities
exchange said net income excluding minority interests rose 19
percent to 261.5 million reais ($157.2 million) from 220 million
reais a year earlier.  BRF Brasil Foods SA (BRFS3 BS) jumped 2.9 percent to 29.53
reais. Valor Economico newspaper reported that billionaire
investor Warren Buffett’s Berkshire Hathaway Inc. started buying
shares in the Brazilian company, the world’s biggest poultry
exporter.    Mills Estruturas e Servicos de Engenharia SA  (MILS3 BS)
declined 2.1 percent to 19.09 reais. The provider of scaffolding
and concrete forms for Brazil’s oil, shipbuilding and
construction industries said controlling shareholder Nacht
Participacoes SA cut its stake in the company to 22 percent from
39 percent.    Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA ’s voting stock
(USIM3 BS) slumped 4 percent to 25.74 reais. Usiminas, as the
steelmaker is known, said in a statement its main shareholders
plan to retain control until at least 2031, following
speculation that rival Cia. Siderurgica Nacional may seek to
boost its stake.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
